      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You can argue that shared cultural understanding is the bedrock of genuine social cohesion. When a community is demographically similar, there is an inherent, immediate level of mutual understanding and shared experience that builds deep, intrinsic trust among residents. This homogeneity allows for the rapid development of strong, localized social networks where everyone shares common values and priorities, leading to higher levels of civic participation within that specific group. In this view, forced integration introduces unnecessary friction and cultural dissonance, which actively undermines the tight-knit harmony that a stable society requires.",
